  "prompt": "Did Bill Clinton cheat on Hillary? If so, how did Hillary deal with it?",
  "response": "Yes, Bill Clinton had an affair with Monica Lewinsky, a White House intern, during his presidency in the 1990s. The affair came to light in 1998, leading to a significant political scandal, including an impeachment trial for Clinton on charges of perjury and obstruction of justice. \n\nHillary Clinton's response to the affair and the subsequent scandal was complex. Initially, she publicly supported her husband, expressing that she believed in his innocence and was committed to their marriage. Over time, however, she navigated a challenging landscape, balancing her role as a political partner, her personal feelings, and public scrutiny.\n\nHillary has spoken about the experience in her books and interviews, acknowledging the pain it caused her but also expressing her determination to work through it. She emphasized the importance of their relationship and their shared commitment to their family and their political goals. The couple ultimately remained together, and Hillary continued to engage in public life, later becoming a prominent political figure in her own right.",
